<h1>Help</h1>
<h2>Warehouse configuration operations</h2>
<ul>
    <li>
        <b>Create location</b> into the warehouse.
    </li>
    <li>
        <b>Modify location</b>
    </li>
    <li>
        <b>Delete location</b> <i>Only can delete a location if hasn't containers or stock.</i>
    </li>
</ul>
<h2>Warehouse stock basic operations</h2>
<ul>
    <li>
        <b>Add stock</b> into a location or a container. <i>Note that if there is another stock into the container/location with the same attributes, the new stock will merge with the existing adding its quantities.</i>
    </li>
    <li>
        <b>Inc/Dec stock</b> to increment or decrement the stock quantity. <i>Note that this option is the best to increment or reduce stock but with add and delete options it can be possible too.</i>
    </li>
    <li>
        <b>Modify stock attributes</b>. <i>Note that the location or quantity can't change with this option, instead use move stock or inc/dec or add or delete stock.</i>
    </li>
    <li>
        <b>Move stock</b> <i>from one location/container to another.</i>
    </li>
    <li>
        <b>Delete stock</b> <i>Note that can delete all the stock. To delete a part of the stock use inc/dec option.</i>
    </li>
</ul>
<h2>Warehouse stock composed operations</h2>
<ul>
    <li>
        <b>Split stock</b> <i>To split, decrement stock and add a new stock.</i>
    </li>
    <li>
        <b>Merge stock</b> <i>To merge one stock with another, decrement/delete the first stock and add a new one to the same location of the other stock.</i>
    </li>
</ul>
<h2>Warehouse stock basic operations</h2>
<ul>
    <li>
        <b>Create container</b> into a location.
    </li>
    <li>
        <b>Modify container</b>
    </li>
    <li>
        <b>Move container</b>
    </li>
    <li>
        <b>Delete container</b> <i>Only can delete a container if hasn't stock.</i>
    </li>
</ul>
